The White House will host a Conference on Bullying Prevention on March 10. President Barack Obama, First Lady Michelle Obama, the Department of Education, and the Department of Health and Human Services will welcome students, parents, and teachers to discuss the effects of bullying and the work being done to address it. The conference will include breakout sessions on effective policies and programs, as well as live chats with Facebook and iVillage. Media coverage will be provided for certain events, and RSVP is required for attendance.